export const STATE_MIDFIX = `A state machine diagram has mainly 4 different components. A small sized circular ellipse denotes a start and end state. The initial and end state have corresponding textboxes to denote them. A rectangle is used to denote a state box, which is a specific moment in the lifespan of an object. It is used to represent any static as well as dynamic situations. The concerned state being shown inside the rectangle with a text element. A decision box contains a condition and is denoted by a diamond. Depending upon the result of the evaluated condition, a new path is taken for program execution. A decision box can have two paths, true or false (denoted by arrow with the text true or false on top/bottom of it using a textbox) from itself to the state which it will go to on trigger of the condition.`;

